    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix potential array out-of-bounds access in get_Np() function\n\n### Summary\nThe `get_Np()` function in `phy_procedures_lte_common.c` could potentially access array elements out of bounds when called with unexpected parameter values, leading to undefined behavior. This fix adds proper parameter validation and bounds checking.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SCHED/phy_procedures_lte_common.c`: Added validation for the `plus1` parameter and bounds checking for array accesses in the `get_Np()` function.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `get_Np()` with `plus1` values greater than 1, the function could attempt to access array indices beyond the valid range, potentially causing memory corruption or incorrect PUCCH resource allocation. The issue manifests as unexpected behavior in PUCCH scheduling and may lead to RRC connection failures or dropped connections in certain scenarios.\n\nTo reproduce:\n1. Call `get_Np(N_RB_DL, nCCE, plus1)` with `plus1 > 1`\n2. Observe potential out-of-bounds array access\n3. Monitor for incorrect PUCCH resource allocation or connection failures\n\nThe fix ensures that `plus1` is properly bounded to valid values (0 or 1) and that all array accesses remain within bounds, preventing undefined behavior while maintaining backward compatibility with existing code.\n"
}